TO ADD THE DIGITS IN A 2 DIGIT NUMBER

two_digit_num = input("Enter a 2 digit number: ")
#Get the first and second digits using subscripting( The subscript operator is defined as square brackets [] ) , then convert it from string to int.
first_num = int(two_digit_num[0])
second_num = int(two_digit_num[1])
#Add the two digits
two_digit_num = first_num + second_num
print(two_digit_num)

#or you can even do it simply without using variables
two_digit_num = input("Enter a 2 digit number: ")
print( int(two_digit_num[0]) + int(two_digit_num[1]) )

o/p: Enter a 2 digit number: 24
     6
